Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Install Python and pytest for the grader
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Prepare initial filesystem state
    mkdir -p /home/user/firewall
    chmod 755 /home/user/firewall

    cat > /home/user/firewall/iptables_rules.v4 <<'EOF'
*filter
:INPUT DROP [0:0]
:FORWARD DROP [0:0]
:OUTPUT ACCEPT [0:0]
-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 22 -j ACCEPT
COMMIT
EOF
    chmod 644 /home/user/firewall/iptables_rules.v4

%labels
    Author      "Generated by ChatGPT"
    Description "Environment for the iptables rule insertion exercise with pytest pre-installed."

%help
This container sets up the initial state for the “iptables rule insertion” task:
• /home/user/firewall exists with 0755 permissions.
• /home/user/firewall/iptables_rules.v4 exists with 0644 permissions and the required starter rules.
Pytest is installed for automated grading.